 sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add cooking apples and chop <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then, with simmering basket in place of measuring cup, cook <b>7 min\/90°C\/speed 1<b>. Insert measuring cup then blend <b>10 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Once pastry has rested for 30 minutes, preheat oven to 220°C. Line chilled pastry case with baking paper and fill with baking beans then blind bake for 10 minutes (220 °C). Remove baking beans and paper then bake for a further 5 minutes (220°C)."},{"content":"Place tin on a wire rack then add reserved apple filling, leaving any excess juice in bowl. Lower oven temperature to 180°C then prepare apple rose."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Apple Rose"},{"content":"Place a bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh in red apple slices, lemon juice and sugar. Remove bowl then mix together well, separating apple pieces."},{"content":"Place water in mixing bowl then insert simmering basket. Add apple slices to simmering basket and cook <b>6-8 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b> until soft and flexible."},{"content":"Working in concentric circles, lay overlapping slices of apple, skin facing outwards, at a slight angle in filling. Repeat, working from the outside into the middle, until all apple slices are used. Bake for 5-10 minutes (180°C) until slightly golden. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Glaze"},{"content":"Place apricot jam and lemon juice in mixing bowl then heat <b>1 min 20 sec\/80°C\/speed 2<b>. Strain through a fine sieve if necessary to remove any lumps, gently brush over apple rose on cooked tart then leave to cool completely in tin."},{"content":"Remove and serve in slices with a scoop of vanilla ice cream, cream or crème fraîche."}],"basicInfo":["advanced","40m","1h 40m","10 slices"]}